  guid: 71622f50-0d26-4712-a35d-6ce9a3feb56b
  itemName: teared fragment #1
  description: "The Rupture cannot be sealed by force of will alone. It was never
    forced open \u2014 it was invited.\r\n\r\nWhat has been called can be uncalled,
    if the caller's mark is undone.\r\n\r\nThree fragments of the Undoing must be
    spoken as one. Worthless apart. Together, in the place where the Rupture was
    born, they form the Counter-Word that Hastur cannot cross.\r\n\r\nThe Seal-Bearer
    must stand in the epicenter. Not near it. In it.\r\n\r\nThe cicatrices on the
    hands of the one who opened the gate must be \u2014\r\n\r\n[The page tears here.
    The rest is missing.]\r\n\r\nIn the margin, a woman's handwriting:\r\n\"Find
    E. She knows the rest. \u2014 E.M.\""
  icon: {fileID: -8343043332886100755, guid: 3492328cc64983b4f98886e6d804e05b, type: 3}
  itemType: 1
